JOHANNESBURG – Scores of people defied cold weather on Wednesday to pay tribute at an official memorial service to the fallen struggle stalwart Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. "Zizojik'izinto wen'ukhalelani"#WinnieMemorial pic.twitter.com/iul9L2CX1b Most donned in ANC regalia. High-profile guests, dignitaries and scores of ordinary South Africans attended the service in Soweto. The struggle icon died peacefully at Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg last Monday, surrounded by her family and loved ones. Click through the gallery in the box above for pictures. eNCA